Dear Merchant:
Effective immediately, your merchant account referenced above has been
suspended for processing due to excessive declines.

Pursuant to Section 14 of your Merchant Processing Agreement, CardConnect is
authorized to suspend processing activity in the event that your account exceeds fraud or
other Card Brand standards.

issues. In order to minimize potential risk exposure to CardConnect while we
investigate the cause of the transaction failures, your merchant account will be
suspended.

Please contact CardConnect Risk Management at 877.828.0720 with any questions.

account referenced above.

JD,
We clearly have some very different ways we handle errors. I think it is safe to say you
probably have about 1,000 merchants for every 1 of ours. For some reason, your company
continues to report errors on transactions that are not necessarily unique to your company,
but are not reported to us. This has happened on more than one occasion, and it continues
to happen. I also find it a bit perplexing that our merchants can submit tokenization requests
through your gateway, but if the system detects an error, our partner and merchant
integrations are just shut off without warning, as was the case tonight. You also did this with:
BLUUR _ and BLUUR _ Most of the time, we find out about an error from one of
our partners/merchants, so we look foolish. It would be greatly appreciated if you could
work toward getting to the bottom of the connectivity issues, and if they cannot be resolved,
notify us with a little more detail as to the root cause.
